# CCMR Weekly Workbook — FAQ

*Answers to common questions about the workbook, the data, and how to use it. For a quick start, see the [One-Pager Guide](CCMR-On-Track-Weekly_One-Pager.md).*

---

## Getting started

### How do I get the woorkbook, and how often?
You receive a refreshed workbook on your campus's configured weekly schedule. Delivery location is set during district onboarding (commonly Google Drive, Box, or a shared folder). Automated email may not work for some districts due to server-side restrictions, so confirm your delivery method with your district contact.

### How do I confirm I'm looking at the right file?
Check the **Menu tab**, which shows your campus name and the week (e.g., "Lake Travis HS — 3/31/2026"). Always save the workbook to your team's shared location so everyone works from the same copy.

---

## Using the workbook

### How do I filter to just my caseload?
The **Counselors** and **Advisors** tabs give you caseload-level rollups by employee. 


### What's the recommended way to use it each week?
Orient (what changed), diagnose (who needs attention), act (assign interventions with clear owners), and revisit the same view next week to check movement. A 15–30 minute weekly meeting is the intended rhythm.

### Can I build a list to hand off to staff?
Yes. Filter All Data to the students you care about, then copy/paste into an email or a separate tracker. The workbook is designed to support action assignment even when the assignment itself happens outside the file.

### Why don't my filters on one tab change the Summary?
By design. Filters apply **only within the current tab.** The Summary always reflects the full campus so it stays a stable reference point. Charts within a tab will update as you filter that tab.

