## Trust, quality, and troubleshooting

### Why are some columns hidden?
Columns are hidden when the underlying data is either **not available** or **not yet reliable** for your campus. Hiding them keeps the workbook credible and prevents decisions based on bad data. As data quality improves, hidden columns can be turned back on.

### What do I do when a student record looks incorrect?
Don't act on the questionable value. Submit a ticket through the support portal (the **Get Help** tab) with the student and field in question. Corrections are made upstream in the source systems, not by editing the workbook — editing your copy won't fix it and the change will be overwritten at the next refresh.

### Can I edit the workbook?
You can filter, sort, and copy data freely, and you can keep your own notes. But remember the file is **regenerated each week**, so any edits you make to the data or layout won't carry forward. Track assignments and notes in a separate place if you need them to persist.

### Which fields are calculated versus reported directly?
TSI Met (Math, ELAR, Overall), the "Met by" labels, GPA bands, and some readiness/college-prep labels are **calculated inside the workbook.** Most other fields (roster, demographics, scores, EOC results, pipeline status) are reported directly from source data. Calculated fields use consistent definitions week to week so you don't have to reinterpret them each refresh.

### Will the workbook always have the same tabs?
Release 1 includes Menu, Summary, All Data, TSI By Assessment, Counselors, Advisors, and Grade Levels. **Release 2** adds more topic tabs (CCMR Status/Trends, IBC Progress, Advanced Coursework, Dual Credit, College Credentials, Postsecondary Enrollment/Pipeline, and Path Form Completion). New tabs are added without breaking existing ones.

